ls, whether of ruins or intact spaces, have been assumed to be “easily legible”; that is, they have been assumed to be vehicles of the authentic. Yet rubble and other models should be theorized as complex simulacra of abstract realities and catalysts of memories. Miniature Monuments thus tackles a haunting paradox: building ruins. The book elucidates how utterly contingent processes of crumbling and collapse (the English words for the Latin ruina) came to command such great interest in modern Europe that tremendous efforts were taken to uncover, render, and, most of all, recreate ruins.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aHistorical modelsxGermany. 0aHistorical models. 0aHistoriographyxGermany. 0aHistoriographyzGermany. 4aErinnerung. 4aGeschichte, deutsche. 4aKulturgeschichte. 4aRuinen. 4aStadtgeschichte. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh  aGerman history.  acultural history.  amemory.  aruins.  aurban history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA History 2000 - 2014z9783110635836oZDB-23-GHI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW0 cEPUBz97831103683450 cprintz978311030385840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030409140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110304091423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110304091/original  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_E